A seven-year-old boy tragically passed away in hospital after he was knocked over by a vehicle on Sparks Road near Barns Road around 1pm yesterday. Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the lifeless body on the pavement.Operations Director, Garrith Jamison said, &#8220;On assessment the child was in cardiac arrest, immediately CPR was started and Advanced Life Support interventions were administered on the scene to the young boy. Miraculously paramedics got a pulse back. The child was then placed on a special stretcher and rushed through to Chief Albert Luthuli Hospital in a critical condition where a trauma team was awaiting the child s arrival.&#8221;Sadly the little boy passed away shortly after his arrival.